Commentary: over the wicket, touch short and straightening on leg stump, tucked down safely from the crease
Commentary_short: SM Curran to Bavuma, no run

Commentary: angled across on a length, Bavuma makes bit of room and jabs into the covers
Commentary_short: SM Curran to Bavuma, no run

Commentary: edged past slip for a boundary! Indeterminate prod from Bavuma but the ball doesn't carry, Ben Stokes stuck out a hand but it skipped past his right ankle and away, fine of third man
Commentary_short: SM Curran to Bavuma, FOUR runs

Commentary: shortish and pulled, a flat swat out to the deep square sweeper
short and wide in the channel outside off, de Kock leans back and happy-slaps it to man at the deep point
Commentary_short: SM Curran to de Kock, 1 run

Commentary: oh dear, that's an unforced error... attempting to scoop and Bavuma gloves it through to the keeper! Tried to get funky early doors and he's instead heading for an early bath (and why not? He won't have to field for an hour or so). Just a length ball in the channel but that looked premeditated from Bavuma, let down by poor execution
Dismissal_text: T Bavuma c †Buttler b SM Curran 5 (5b 1x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: back of a length, kisses the surface and flies off the outside edge! Goes wide of Stokes, needed a second slip in, but de Kock's furtive glance back only confirms one to third man
shortish, 139kph/86mph and rising in the corridor, Faf is across and shoulders arms
Commentary_short: Archer to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: length ball, du Plessis comes forward on off stump and shows it a straight bat in defence
Commentary_short: Archer to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: pitched up, 140kph/87mph, gets a touch too straight and du Plessis is off the mark with a nimble clip through midwicket
stays back, skidding into the pads as he looks to work across the line
Commentary_short: Archer to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: bangs away on a length, 139kph in the channel and Faf settles for a calm dab into the covers
Commentary_short: Archer to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: pitched up and driven, nicely played and it looks like it might have the beating of mid-off... only for Chris Jordan to pounce on it cat-like and prevent a boundary
Commentary_short: TK Curran to de Kock, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, 132kph/82mph and du Plessis mistimes an attempted cut down into the pitch
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: slower ball in the channel, Faf waits and steers it behind square, de Kock had come haring down looking for one... had to throw himself for the crease as the throw came back to the bowler's end
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: pitched up and du Plessis punches it back, Curran fields in his follow through
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: length ball on off and it's lumped over the covers, just a single to the sweeper
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, 1 run

Commentary: fullish on the stumps from over the wicket, QdK clips towards mid-on
Commentary_short: TK Curran to de Kock, 1 run

Commentary: short of a length, 139kph/86mph and de Kock forces this through midwicket for a couple
hooned! Easy breezy pick-up from de Kock and that is the first six of the day! Up and over, right out of the meat, and he lands the ball in the empty seats at deep square leg
Commentary_short: Archer to de Kock, SIX runs

Commentary: short of a length outside off, Quinny steers this through backward point
on the stumps and du Plessis works it into the leg side
skelped through the leg side! Pitched up, 143kph/89mph on on the pads, de Kock hammers another boundary to the midwicket fence
Commentary_short: Archer to de Kock, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball, on the stumps, de Kock shows this a straight bat
Commentary_short: Archer to de Kock, no run

Commentary: swung away over cow! Cutter from Curran and du Plessis dispenses with the niceties and belts it over the fence and into the construction site!
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, SIX runs

Commentary: superb stuff, smoked down the ground for four! Full and in the slot and Faf wafts it back over Curran's head
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, FOUR runs

Commentary: creams six more, flat over deep square leg! Some powerful tonkage from the former captain
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, SIX runs

Commentary: full and wide, driven through the covers, 'Two! Two! Two!' is the call and they get back despite de Kock's slip at the striker's end
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, 2 runs

Commentary: length, width on offer again, du Plessis crunches this in front of the sweeper, Sam doing well to save his brother a couple
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, 2 runs

Commentary: pitched up and munched through midwicket for four more! Big old bottom-handed mow and it flies away, even as the bat skewed in his hands
Commentary_short: TK Curran to du Plessis, FOUR runs

Commentary: clubbed back through mid-on, that's nearly taken out Faf! The senior man is left on his backside by an exocet from Quinny
Commentary_short: SM Curran to de Kock, FOUR runs

Commentary: in the channel, shortish and de Kock cuts, comes off the bottom edge
Commentary_short: SM Curran to de Kock, no run

Commentary: angled in on the stumps, QdK whips it away through midwicket for one
Commentary_short: SM Curran to de Kock, 1 run

Commentary: round the wicket, CSK bowling to CSK, du Plessis jumps across and nurdles off his front pad through square leg
Commentary_short: SM Curran to du Plessis, 1 run

Commentary: short outside off, de Kock slaps this to backward point
Commentary_short: SM Curran to de Kock, no run

Commentary: length, 128kph/79mph and he comes across, stabs through the covers to the boundary rider
Commentary_short: SM Curran to de Kock, 1 run

Commentary: over the wicket, lobs up a googly that spins across from outside leg, Quinny nudges off his pads for one
tossed up on the stumps, du Plessis works it through midwicket
dragged down and skidding on, de Kock swats it to leg for one more
loopy legbreak, drifting on to leg stump, Faf stokes one more down the ground
quicker ball, de Kock punches it off the back foot through cover
flat leggie pushed through outside off and du Plessis chops down to complete an over of singles
back of a length on the stumps, 129kph/80mph and it skips up to strike du Plessis in the gut. Missed with a forearm jab and took it right on the abs (not the ABs)
Commentary_short: Jordan to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: short length, this is shovelled away through backward square leg for a couple
full on off, du Plessis likes it there: whumped straight back down the ground! Du Plessis hits through the line, picks up another boundary
Commentary_short: Jordan to du Plessis, FOUR runs

Commentary: goes shorter again, worked off the body
round the wicket, full at 139kph/86mph and sliding on to the pads, de Kock whips to deep midwicket
pitched full on off, Faf picks out cover on the drive
Commentary_short: Jordan to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: pushes through the googly, slightly leg side and Buttler can't take it cleanly - called wide, too
floated up on the stumps and steered through the covers
flights this, goes wide of the off stump and de Kock swings it down the ground, a misfield at long-on brings them two
floated up and nudged leg side
Commentary_short: Rashid to de Kock, no run

Commentary: swing and a miss from de Kock... and England are reviewing for something. Buttler didn't appeal, but Morgan thought there might be a scrape of bat on that. DRS confirms there wasn't
Commentary_short: Rashid to de Kock, no run

Commentary: comes down and twocks this through the covers
flights the googly, du Plessis clips it calmly through mid-on
135kph/83mph, sliding leg side and du Plessis picks him off fine of the fielder! Just a touch for four
Commentary_short: Jordan to du Plessis, FOUR runs

Commentary: pitched up and whisked off the pads down to fine leg

plinked to cover! Jordan makes the breakthrough for England. Tried to hit him off his length, but he didn't get hold of it, sent the ball skimming straight to his counterpart Morgan on the edge of the circle! They were looking pretty untroubled, but Quinny sensed he had to try and crack on
Dismissal_text: Q de Kock c Morgan b Jordan 30 (23b 2x4 1x6) SR: 130.43

Commentary: fullish in the channel, 141kph/88mph and Rassie pushes forward, gets an inside edge to leg
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: on the stumps, Faf gets one more off his thigh pad
Commentary_short: Jordan to du Plessis, 1 leg bye

Commentary: pitched up and worked through square leg - halfway through the overs and this is nicely poised
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: flighted, the legbreak spins a touch as he covers the line and taps it away
Commentary_short: Rashid to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: tossed up and tapped into the off side coming forwards
Commentary_short: Rashid to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: googly, sliding leg side, Rassie nudges it for a single behind square
Commentary_short: Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: drops a touch short and this is cut off the back foot for one
flighted, straightening outside off, leans out and steers into a gap
Commentary_short: Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: Rashid wheels away around off stump, Faf is into line and punches through cover
short outside off, du Plessis steers this down into the off side
short of a length, RvD² is across and rolls his wrists on a pull, front knee cocked in the air
Commentary_short: Archer to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, punched in front of square and it takes a good bit of work from Bairstow on the rope to prevent four - that's a half-century for du Plessis, nevertheless, leading the way for SA here
short ball, snorting at Rassie is he drops the hands outside off
Commentary_short: Archer to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: dug in again and RvD² pulls without timing, picks out midiwcket
Commentary_short: Archer to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: back of a length on the stumps and Rassie is across and nurdles behind square to keep the strike
Commentary_short: Archer to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: loops up the legbreak, tempting van der Dussen to go after him, attempts the slog-sweep but fails to connect as it spins through to Buttler
Commentary_short: Rashid to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: nailed this time, hammers a googly up and over deep midwicket! Properly clonked beyond the ropes, and that'll ease the pressure on van der Dussen
Commentary_short: Rashid to van der Dussen, SIX runs

Commentary: poked into a gap in the off side
Commentary_short: Rashid to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: tossed up and swung away through midwicket for a couple
pushed through, stops a touch in the surface, du Plessis prods it back watchfully
Commentary_short: Rashid to du Plessis, no run

Commentary: tossed up and tapped into the covers - tidy figures of 4-0-27-0 for Rashid
shortish and whipped away on the pull, into a gap for two
Commentary_short: SM Curran to du Plessis, 2 runs

Commentary: back of a length on the stumps, spliced for a single, du Plessis groans at the connection
Commentary_short: SM Curran to du Plessis, 1 run

Commentary: fuller length, maybe a cutter and dinked into the leg side, SCurran goes scurrying after it
Commentary_short: SM Curran to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: short ball, du Plessis swats leg side... but holes out to deep square leg! That's a handy wicket for England, with du Plessis well set and driving the SA innings. Looks like Curran took pace off even as he went short and Faf had to manufacture the power to the longer boundary. Well taken on the run by Jordan, who doesn't drop many
Commentary_short: SM Curran to du Plessis, OUT
Dismissal_text: F du Plessis c Jordan b SM Curran 58 (40b 4x4 2x6) SR: 145.00

Commentary: banged in, this one is too short as it balloons through to the keeper
Commentary_short: SM Curran to van der Dussen, 1 wide

Commentary: nudged off the pads, Jordan has to sprint in from the rope, and Rassie safely gets back for two
back of a length, 129kph/80mph and it kicks up at van der Dussen, who can only tap it down towards the crease
Commentary_short: SM Curran to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: length, bit of width on offer, Klaasen cuts forcefully for a couple to get off the mark straight away
fired in straighter, nudged towards midwicket
pace off but straying leg side as RvD² aims a big ole swing across the line... gets the extra
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 wide

Commentary: length ball, but fired down the leg side for another wide
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 wide

Commentary: shortish outside off, slower ball and van der Dussen can only cut for one to deep point
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: pace off again, wide of the stumps, but Klaasen times it nicely, steered behind square for four! Beats the man with deft placement
short of a length and clubbed in front of deep point for a few more
fired into the blockhole, Rassie can only dig it out through mid-on for one
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: starts with a low full toss, tapped off the toe of the bat into the leg side
Commentary_short: TK Curran to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: pace off, Klaasen attempts to force it, can't beat the bowler in his follow through
Commentary_short: TK Curran to Klaasen, no run

Commentary: pitched up outside off, chipped down through ground through mid-off coming across
back of a length, not much pace to work with as he swings away a pull
slower-ball bouncer, RvD² jumps to try and put as much as he can into his pull, just gets a couple between the leg-side sweepers
Commentary_short: TK Curran to van der Dussen, 2 runs

Commentary: kaboom! Spanked into the bleachers over wide long-on! Full in the slot and Rassie collars him again, more punishment for TC as the ball clatters on to the concrete
Commentary_short: TK Curran to van der Dussen, SIX runs

Commentary: shortish and skidding through wide of the off, gets a toe end on it and Buttler does well to prevent it scuttling away
Commentary_short: SM Curran to Klaasen, no run

Commentary: goes for the wide yorker, but Klaasen plays it well! Shuffled across and jammed the bat down, got it past short third man and away
Commentary_short: SM Curran to Klaasen, FOUR runs

Commentary: short ball on the stumps and he pulls into a gap
pitched up and struck down the ground coming forwards
flung full and wide, 134kph/83mph but RvD² picks out cover on the drive
Commentary_short: SM Curran to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: SCurran's bumper does it again! Got up higher than Klaasen was expecting and his slash across the line only results in a thin edge through to the keeper! Third wicket of the piece for Big Sam, England applying the brakes once more
Dismissal_text: H Klaasen c †Buttler b SM Curran 20 (12b 2x4 0x6) SR: 166.66

Commentary: pitched up in the channel, punched through the covers coming across
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: fired in full, right up on the bootlaces and van Biljon can only clip it through square for one
Jordan sprays this down the leg side
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 wide

Commentary: clobbered over deep midwicket!
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: clobbered over deep square! Full but not full enough, didn't look like he'd got hold of it but it went flat and far enough
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, SIX runs

Commentary: comes across and jabs one into the covers
Commentary_short: Jordan to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: punched back and Jordan grabs the ball in his follow through, lobs it at the stumps in one motion with van der Dussen scrambling... and gives up a run in the process
glides in and hits the pitch, 142kph/88mph and whipped into the leg side
full on off, Rassie heaves to leg and picks up one more to the deep midwicket sweeper running in
Commentary_short: Archer to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: attempted yorker on off stump and van Biljon can't get under it, chopped to extra cover

Archer strikes, the full bunger does it! In the arc but Rassie can't get it out of the park, instead he miscues a swing to leg and sends it looping to deep backward square! Archer knows that wasn't his best ball, by a stretch, heads back to his mark
Commentary_short: Archer to van der Dussen, OUT
Dismissal_text: HE van der Dussen c Malan b Archer 37 (28b 0x4 3x6) SR: 132.14

Commentary: quick on off, 149kph/92mph and van Biljon hops into line, taps it down for a scurried single
round the wicket, full length in the channel, Linde is off the mark with a tip-and-run into the covers
goes full and wide, aiming for the tramlines from round the wicket... too wide
full toss and this is clumped over extra cover! Linde grins as he piles into another wide delivery and picks up four
Commentary_short: TK Curran to Linde, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on the stumps this time and whisked leg side
pace off, short length and it sits up as van Biljon swings hard, gets it into a gap for two
Commentary_short: TK Curran to van Biljon, 2 runs

Commentary: fired down the leg side
Commentary_short: TK Curran to van Biljon, 2 wides

Commentary: full toss once again, Linde gives it some pongo over deep square! Poor ball but he really dispatched it with aplomb
Commentary_short: TK Curran to Linde, SIX runs

Commentary: short of a length in the channel, pace off and he swings and misses this time
Commentary_short: TK Curran to Linde, no run

Commentary: bowled 'im! Full and quick, 132kph/82mph and hits the base of off stump! Linde's feet didn't move and Curran brings it back just a touch with the final ball of the innings. Tough night for him, and that looks a competitive score
Dismissal_text: GF Linde  b TK Curran 12 (6b 1x4 1x6) SR: 200.00

Commentary: round the wicket, tweaked onto a middle-and-leg line and grips a touch. Roy flinches with stiff wrists, back to the bowler, on the bounce ... oooh...

shorter, wider, Roy flaps into a wild cut, and snicks through to the keeper! Another first-over dismissal for England's Mr All or Nothing ... and Linde has made his mark in no uncertain terms! Glee unbounded! And that's opened this chase up alright! He's never been at his most comfortable against spin first-up, and those hard hands paid the price!
Dismissal_text: JJ Roy c †de Kock b Linde 0 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: tapped into the off side, leaning to the pitch
head over the ball, eased out to point
tweaking down the leg side, not the best ball, but an even worse shot! The ball dies as Malan turns his wrists, and almost scoops straight to square leg!
on the back foot, a compact poke to cover, and that's the end of an outstanding debut over, if not a maiden over! Now then ...this game is afoot!
don't think he pulled out of that one, but the shot was much the same! Beaten for pace before he'd really decided on the stroke!
fast and full, thudding the pads as Rabada snakes an inducker back into the left-hander. Feisty
anchored on the back foot, a firm thud of bat into the off side, but straight at point
cracked with intent into the covers, on the back foot again, half-stopped as mid-off tidies up
back and across, sharp pace from Rabada on a full length, and pressed out to point
width for Malan to rattle into a scything drive, but he picks out point again. Good shot for none as they say. But nothing wrong with the timing there
width outside off, Buttler slaps an upper-cut of a drive out to deep cover
advancing to the back-of-a-length ball outside off, thumped at the top of the bounce, but gathered at backward point
oops, that was a bit wild! Hendricks lost his footing, and his line, as he dragged the ball way down, banged in nearer his toes than Malan's!
shaping into the pads, and this time Malan's timing finds some placement to go with it! Clipped sweetly, on the up through midwicket!
gives himself room, but that's a fine line, rising on off stump, and eluding a flashing cut
flipped off the pads, and worked to the leg side
pumped into the covers, and another single
makes room, and slaps the cutter emphatically through the covers! This is an ominous start from Malan, he's easing into his night's work
tremendous placement! Compact stance, meeting the ball cleanly with a sweet chiselled drive, bissecting two fielders at cover and mid-off
timed once again, but straight to backward point
drilled out to the off side for another single
too straight, Buttler shuffles in his stance, and clips very fine through backward square. He's up and running now, as England settle into their chase
poked to mid-on, tight line to complete an otherwise leaky over
... hmmm .... we'll have that one again. A filthy leg-side wide, hardly hits the cut strip

flogged off a full length and Buttler's holed out! Ngidi gets it right alright second-up, a poor shot by his high standards, the ball was in his arc, but his mega-wrists let him down on this occasion, as the cross-seam delivery spliced high into the covers, to dent England's chase once more!
Dismissal_text: JC Buttler c Klaasen b Ngidi 7 (6b 1x4 0x6) SR: 116.66

Commentary: outside off, just back of a length but a very tight line. Beaten outside off
guided behind point to rotate the strike
back of a length, slower ball, opens the face and nudged through backward point. No fielder there!
angled bat, on the front foot, and a loud bellow of 'no!'
slower bouncer, Bairstow rocks back, and rolls his wrists on a very delayed pull. Settles for the single
round the wicket, hitting a good length with a bit of tweak, chopped to the off side
straighter lines, Bairstow waits on the back foot and nudges to leg with a closed face. So slow off the deck

stunning catch at square leg! Malan climbed into a pre-meditated sweep, clawing the ball from outside off, but Rabada watched it all the way, dived forward, inviting a ball in the teeth, and scooped up the offering to give Linde figures of 2 for 2 in nine balls!
Dismissal_text: DJ Malan c Rabada b Linde 19 (20b 3x4 0x6) SR: 95.00

Commentary: up on the toes, pressed back to the bowler
outside off, fired across the left-hander, and no stroke offered
standing tall, on the back foot, vertical blade, none shall pass. Stokes likes to take his time to get started. He's doing just that. But what figures for the new boy!
on the hips, flinched to the man on the 45
leg-sided once more, tucked off the legs and finds the gap this time
bottom-handed push through long-on, Stokes is off the mark with a jogged single
down on one knee, lifting a ramp over the shoulder, and that's placed well through fine leg, where Ngidi gallumphs after the ball and claws it back well
another single for Stokes, England content to take their time for now
tight leg-sided line, Bairstow wears it on the front pad as he attempts a flick to leg
high elbowed prod into the covers. Linde's mega-arm is keeping a lid on the scoring
wider line to the leftie, but the ball is coming so slowly off the deck that timing is a lottery. Stokes flaps into the off side
this time, some intent! Footwork, to the pitch, hands through the line, biffed over the covers!
a huge wind-up, on the charge again, but he can't time it as the ball bobbles off the splice to mid-on
rotating the strike with a more measured clip off the pads to deep midwicket
worked to the leg side, and they come back for the second. But the damage to Linde's figures is minimal
fired outside off, too wide that time
levers from Bairstow! Full length on a wide line, but Jonny is loitering on the back foot, and launches his bat through the line, over long-on!
that's gone too! Listen to the report of willow! No doubt where that was heading! Outside off, room to swing into the slog-sweep, and dumped on the grass at midwicket!
tighter line, as Shamsi drags his length back, and nudged to the on-side
sharp turn from a middle-and-leg line to the leftie, clipped to mid-on

scuffed through the leg side again, and so nearly a blinder from Faf! Hard and flat from Bairstow, and du Plessis at wide long-on, sticks out his left hand, nearly clings on, but in the end does well to save six as he topples over the rope with the ball still in play
tucked to the on-side to keep the strike. A lively over in so many ways...
back of a length, Stokes pounds in a pull but is disgusted with his timing as he nearly flings his bat away in his followthrough. Deep midwicket tidies
tapped to backward point for the single
That's the timing Stokes was looking for! Rifled into the stands at deep midwicket, hitting with the wind, picking the ball up outside off, on the slog sweep, and that's flown!
tossed up outside off, Stokes charges, and has to check back to the bowler, after accepting he was beaten in flight. Well bowled
lines up the reverse sweep but can't nail the placement, or the timing
back of a length, clipped to the on-side, Linde's spell is done, 2 for 20 in four overs is not to be sniffed at!
back of a length, tucked to the on-side for the single
width, from back of a length, Stokes flashes a cut to the cover sweeper
Twanged into the stands! Ngidi hits the deck, and Bairstow hits Ngidi! Anchored in the crease, anticipating the skiddy back-of-a-lengther, and smoking it over midwicket!
wide outside off, Bairstow leathers a cut-drive, but slightly off the toe as it plugs short of the cover sweeper
back of a length, slower ball, well served-up, as Stokes advanced to meet him, so he dragged the length back and nearly forced a mix-up with the batsman so far down the pitch
sitting back in the crease this time, thwacked with a cross-blade to deep midwicket. England keep the pot boiling
outside off, cracked with intent but not a lot of timing to deep backward point
swings into a pull, misses it entirely and wears the ball on his bicep, but they all count as Stokes hustles him through for the single. Misread the cutter on that occasion
honked on the up, leaning back for extra power, and outside-edged to third man
battered with murderous power through the leg side! Klaasen does brilliantly to get a hand on it as he dives at deep midwicket (not a catch), but the ball still rattles through to the rope
gosh, that is cheeky from Jonny! Open face, pure timing, as Hendricks fires it out wide, and he just uses the pace to launch it over third man!

a swing and a miss, no contact on that frantic mow. This is getting tasty, as England's run-rate just begins to draw level with South Africa's, who were 96 for 2 at this stage... but who don't bat to 11!
Stokes still lacking a touch in timing as he attempts to find a gap on the off side, and fails
who needs timing when you've got power! Stokes pulls out the sod-it mow, and launches a massive slog-sweep high over long-on!
swept off his feet this time! Stokes made room, and Klaasen followed him, speared into the retreating pads to cramp his intentions
flicked to the leg side
on a full length, middle-stump line, Bairstow drives with poise for the single to cover
into the pads, and smoked over backward square! Now that was timing from Stokes, who barely followed through, but nailed the flick, hard and flat into the advertising hoardings
slower ball, another cutter, dragged into the middle of the pitch and eluding another wipe to leg
bottom-handed thump to long-off. Meeting the full, wide line with purpose
very wide line, on a full length, decent ball to a man in a mood, Stokes settles for the tapped cut to deep point and a single
banged in short, good option but over head-height
mowed to the leg side, steepling top-edge, but safe! De Kock back-pedals but the ball plugs way beyond him at fine leg
whoosh! Jonny was peering towards the Antarctic by the end of that one, wider line, outside the eyeline, and through to the keeper

clobbered through wide mid-on to bring up Bairstow's fifty! Probably the wrong option from Hendricks, tried to finish the over with a length ball, but he was made to regret it with a blistering swipe!

holed out to long-on! Linde is the man just inside the rope, who barely has to move as Stokes winds into the long-hop, could have sent it anywhere, but it ended up in the new boy's breadbasket! And is that a glimmer for South Africa?
Dismissal_text: BA Stokes c Linde b Shamsi 37 (27b 1x4 3x6) SR: 137.03

Commentary: nudged to the on side to open his account
closing the face on a full length, a loud shout of 'no!'
sharp spin as Morgan leans onto the off-stump line, poked into the covers
flashed out to the cover sweeper, another single to get the skipper's juices flowing
hauled to the on-side, big turn from off to leg as Bairstow dances into a low-handed pull
sharp pace, back of a length, Bairstow pulls but straight to midwicket

full and inswinging, so close! It looked for a moment as though it had cannoned off Jonny's pads into the stumps, but that shape into the right-hander is why the lbw is turned down. Sharp delivery though!
outside off, can't connect with this one
swished into the leg side, full length into the legs, and flicked behind square
banged in short, slower ball, cunning work. Bairstow hops to meet it, but can't lay bat on ball. 'That's your one for the over,' says the ump

... Bairstow knew this would be fuller! Winding into a powerful slog-drive, high over the leg-side, and plugging inches inside the rope! Bairstow is carrying this fight, but that was a fine over from SA's gun. And he has one more of the four to come...
flicked to the on-side, just the single as Morgan gets YJB back on strike. The rate has ticked past two a ball...
bottom-handed magnificence! Full length, swinging away, and somehow that's been nailed through the covers, with one hand coming off the bat as he has to stretch to reach it!
shouts of 'catch!' but that's short of deep midwicket as Bairstow leathers a flat clip off the legs
Crumbs, that's gone wrong! So wide it didn't hit the cut strip, on latitude or longitude! A direct delivery to fine leg, and that helps the cause!
pummelled over midwicket, and now Morgan joins the fray! And fray is the mot juste for this over, it's rather going wrong ...
short and wide, too wide ... Hendricks is losing his grip here ...
fires in the fuller length, but the width is so inviting for the in-form Bairstow! He simply opens his face again, and plinks it through third man!
sliding past the legs, a better ball by the standards of what's preceded it, but another wide...
back of a length, shaping into the pads, Bairstow nurdles to backward square, to end a 28-run game-wrecking over...
back of a length, slower ball, Morgan waits on the back foot and thumps a cut to point
back of a length, open face, guided through third man

flogged to deep midwicket, and Morgan is gone! Bowled into the deck, no pace as it rose into the skipper's swinging blade, and just a glimmer for South Africa, although England don't exactly have a dearth of batting to come...
Dismissal_text: EJG Morgan c Bavuma b Ngidi 12 (10b 0x4 1x6) SR: 120.00

Commentary: tight line, full length, Bairstow leans forward with a respectful block but still steals the single into the covers

wears it on the lid! Banged in short, and Curran's attempts to wind into a pull ends up hitting him in the grille. Bairstow has no mercy and orders him through for the single, which he makes with a dive. We'll have an interlude for the mandatory concussion test, but he seems fine
Commentary_short: Ngidi to SM Curran, 1 leg bye

Commentary: wafted to the leg side, another single to finish off the over
nutmegged! Very full, and beats Bairstow's dancing feet for pace as he attempts a leg glance
cracked hard across the line as Rabada fires into the legs again. Deep square leg tidies up
slower bouncer, dug into the pitch once more, and out comes a tennis-smash of a pull as Bairstow reaches high to flog it to the leg side. A good finish to this over will keep it very interesting...
width outside off, and Curran nails his launch down the ground! My God, he's got some ticker... had to wait and wait as the pace was off, but he cleared du Plessis by a distance at long-on!
Commentary_short: Rabada to SM Curran, SIX runs

Commentary: up on the toes to cut to the covers, and it's nearly a run a ball now
crunched with a straight bat, clean to long-on, 'one, one,' is Jonny's call. No need to make things happen. Seven to win in the final over iit is...
a roundhouse slog, picking up the width outside off, and hauled through midwicket! This is nearly done now ...

that's the way to finish it! In the slot, monstered over wide long-on to seal it with four balls to spare! Jonny Bairstow has quite possibly solved one of the key puzzles for England ... who can fill the void in the middle-order in their opener-heavy line-up? That's quite the audition.
